body_html:
Thats great! But I think you might have missed out some such as https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/framework/ops.py#L2128
etc.

Don't think you need to revert anything but what I'm saying is that if the .py files for all the ops are not changed this problem with re-occur because someone will regenerate and we'll get the broken links back again. So I guess it would be great if you can look through all the python API docs that were changed in this PR and see if there are corresponding .py documentation that might need to be changed as well.
